Package: vork-relay
Version: [[version]]
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: java21-runtime-headless | java22-runtime-headless | java23-runtime-headless | java24-runtime-headless | java25-runtime-headless
Installed-Size: [[installed-size]]
Maintainer: Vork <relay@vork.sh>
Homepage: https://github.com/vork/vork-relay
Description: Zero-knowledge encrypted authorization form relay
 Vork Relay is a stateless HTTPS relay that allows Vork AI agents running
 inside firewalled or air-gapped environments to request human authorization
 without requiring any inbound firewall holes.
 .
 The relay is cryptographically blind: it stores only AES-256-GCM ciphertext.
 The decryption key is delivered to the user's browser via the URL hash
 fragment, which is never transmitted to the server.
 .
 On first start, the server opens on port 80 and presents a setup wizard
 that obtains a TLS certificate from Let's Encrypt.  After the certificate
 is issued the server restarts on port 443 and automatically renews the
 certificate 30 days before expiry with no downtime.
